            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "The Contoso Electronics Whistleblower Policy emphasizes maintaining a safe and transparent work environment. Key components of the policy include:\n\n1. **Purpose**: Encourage employees, contractors, and third parties to report unethical or illegal activities within the organization.\n   \n2. **Definition**: A whistleblower is any individual reporting illegal, unethical, or non-compliant activities.\n\n3. **Reporting Procedures**:\n   - Contact the Human Resources Department.\n   - Email the Compliance Officer at **compliance@contoso.com**.\n   - Call the Compliance Hotline at **1-800-555-1212**.\n   - Reports can be made anonymously through the hotline.\n\n4. **Details Required in Reports**:\n   - Time and date of the incident.\n   - Individuals involved.\n   - Description of the incident.\n   - Evidence, if available.\n\n5. **Prohibition of Retaliation**:\n   - Strictly prohibits retaliation of any kind against whistleblowers, with disciplinary actions for violators.\n\n6. **Confidentiality**:\n   - Whistleblower identity is kept confidential, as long as it is compliant with the law.\n\n7. **Investigation**:\n   - All reports are investigated promptly and thoroughly.",
                "annotations": [
